title: He rode out Hurricane Otis on his boat. He hasn’t been seen since.
description: Yacht captain Demetrio Felipe is one of scores of people still missing after the powerful storm slammed into Acapulco, Mexico, last week.

title: Israeli strikes on Gaza refugee camp offer glimpse of war’s destruction
description: The strikes on Jabalya show the toll of Israel’s relentless air war and the grave dangers facing civilians as ground forces move deeper into the enclave.

title: Hurricane Otis produced 205 mph gust, among strongest ever measured
description: The ferocious wind is preliminary but would rank among the highest on record if confirmed.

title: What to know about Gaza refugee camps after Israeli strike on Jabalya
description: Israel has attacked refugee camps in Gaza, including the Jabalya camp. Here’s what to know about why there are camps in Gaza, and why Israel says it attacked them.

title: Israel carries out new strikes on Gaza camp as wounded trickle into Egypt
description: The slow flow of a few dozen wounded through the Rafah crossing into Egypt contrasts with the many killed and injured by airstrikes and clashes in northern Gaza.

title: White House nominates Asia lead Kurt Campbell to be Blinken’s deputy
description: President Biden has nominated Kurt Campbell, the architect of his Asia strategy, to be Secretary of State Antony Blinken’s deputy at the State Department.

title: Bolivia cuts diplomatic ties with Israel over attacks in Gaza
description: Soon after Bolivia cut ties, Chile and Colombia said they would recall their ambassadors from Israel over what they described as violations of international humanitarian law.

title: Saudi Arabia becomes sole bidder for 2034 soccer World Cup
description: Australia said it would not make a play to host the men’s tournament, leaving Saudi Arabia as the only bidder and likely host.

title: The Robin Hood-style epic that’s a surprise hit in wartime Ukraine
description: In “Dovbush,” a dashing 18th-century outlaw robs from the foreign overlords and gives to the poor — and also strikes a chord among modern Ukrainians.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Hamas issues list of foreign nationals who may be allowed to leave Gaza
description: Hundreds of foreign nationals and Palestinian dual citizens were told to show up Wednesday morning at the Rafah border crossing into Egypt.

title: Israel leans into World War II rhetoric to justify Gaza war
description: Justifying civilian deaths in Gaza, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu pointed to a British bombing raid almost 80 years ago that killed children.
